caption: Excellent food and staff!
Inspired by the cuisine of northern Baja California, this is in my opinion the best of Bayless' restaurants. The beef short rib is nothing short of magnificent!
Dddddrrreliscious. Great flavors to some classic plates.

I truly enjoyed the ambiance, the food, and the service. I will definitely come again. They are a multilevel restaurant with an absolutely fabulous menu. It is Mexican but they have added a twist to some of the traditional favorites, which make it that much more unique and still as tasty and absolutely delicious. I will come again and I do recommend them!
Great atmosphere, delicious drinks and food, very polite stuff. Upstairs has a beautiful intimate vibe for a perfect date night. I will definitely go back!
Food was delicious! Happy hour: has 2 items... They have a reservation fee for covid then a covid fee on the receipt Strict time limit Veryyyy expensive: 1 sweet potato = $12
Had a great time there on Valentine's day food and drinks were good.

We came for a date night and had such an amazing experience! We ordered the oysters as an appetizer which were soooooooooo good, we ordered more! We had the striped sea bass as an entree and it was very delicious!! Omggg the food was absolutely amazing! Cocktails were very tasty as well. We will be back!

Presentation was on point for every dish. The short rib falls off the bone and the shrimp cocktail is bright in flavor. The smores pie reminds me of Mexican style hot chocolate and is a refreshing rendition of a simple dessert.
Food and dining experience were top notch. We will be returning customers.
OMG delicious mexican food!!!  Love it!!  Can't wait to be back 💓💓
Sea food was amazing

Lena Brava is always a culinary adventure. The tent is warm enough and safe to eat out. I loved every bit of my dishes, and the oysters were so delicate, perfectly seasoned, and flavorful that we ordered the second round. I am happy this restaurant stays in business safe and sound.

One of my favorite restaurants in West Loop. Ordered 2 entradas, 1 seafood, 1 meat, 1 side, and 1 dessert—almost all of them were exceptional. Especially Chicken al Carbon and Wood Oven Tart—they are just heavenly. Will come here regularly, at least in the foreseeable future.  Update on second visit: tried some other dishes and not as good as those in my first visit. Plus their service this time really sucks. Disappointed because my expectation was too high, but ok. 4.5 star suits this place the best. P.S. No restaurants can beat Aba so far in west loop area lol...
Awesome drinks and solid atmosphere.

Every dish we ordered was perfect. The menu is unique and most of the dishes are shareable. Portions are not too small and not too large. They were perfect. Pan de Campo was my favorite  appetizer. The short rib was perfect when I had it with Bok choy & butternut. Cocktails were good and the service was great. It's a great place and worth checking out if you're travelling or local.
Fabulous food and service. Wood roasted oysters, charred avocado,  lobster roll with shaved fennel and pickled jalapeño. Great mixed drinks
Best skirt steak I've ever had.

I suggested to my co-workers that we go grab a quick dinner here. What a mistake, 3 of 4 ordered salmon and all of us got frozen pieces of fish. We returned it back to the kitchen and were told it can't be cooked... what? We ended up leaving hungry. Now I'm searching my car for a granola bar before i have to go in to our next meeting. Unbelievable!
Good site for delicious mexican food. good place to catch up with friends. the service here is above par.
mexican food at this place - great. Entered near ten, it was not crowded. Looking forward to coming back with my coworkers.
The food was amazing! The service was impeccable. I will definitely be back.

Service and food quality have significantly reduced. Was informed at chekin that we could only stay 2 hours. Ended up being there for almost 3 hours becuase the food too so long to come. Great cocktails.
Good but small portions and pricey
mexican food here - super good. I love visiting here. The service here is friendly. Prices were fair. Makes me feel like I in Nashville again.
Awesome food and dessert.
Octopus brochetas were amazing...sauce with Chorizo complemented very well
Ceviche and ribs are sooooooo good. Great food and awesome ambience!

We dined here this afternoon for my birthday and we had a great time. In the beginning we went up to the host stand and we asked if that was the leña brava hoststand, and we were just told to go into the restaurant, once inside we approached a server which then led us back to the host stand we were just at. The server tried to get the attention of the hostess as she and the other hostess were having a conversation, the server tapped the hostess on the shoulder at least three to four times until she finally looked back and asked me if I had a reservation, she was very polite and welcoming once the server had to direct us back to her, I just didnt understand why we didn't get that in the beginning when I went up to the host sand. Immediately after we sat down we had a great time, we loved our server, he was great, unfortunately I don't remember his name, but service was great, food was phenomenal! drinks? phenomenal . We had the octopus dish which was one of our favorite, we had the leña ceviche which was also pretty great, we also had the short rib, which basically fell off the bone it was THAT good. The hubby had the skirt steak which he also enjoyed. Overall an amazing experience, thank you Rick Bayless, another extremely satisfied customer.
Loved the food and service, but super expensive!.... 4 drinks 2 appetizers and 2meals was was $200.... but you cannot make a bad Choice my favorite was the “Tamales” and the “camarones a la Mexicana”
Wow! Every single dish that we ordered was out of this world. DEFINITELY recommend the ceviche, the grilled oysters, grilled pineapple and the octopus. I could eat those oysters everyday, amazing!
Wonderful food!

One of my favorite restaurants in Chicago.  All of their dishes are delicious and the method of the way they cook them is something that you cannot replicate in your home kitchen.  I highly recommend the dishes below  Lena Ceviche - the juice is just unreal. You would want to empty out the entire bowl.  Charred Avocado - great texture and smooth.  Chicken Al Carbon - marinate is the key and there is flavor in every part of the chicken all the way to the bone.  Plantains - soft and creamy.  The Skirt Steak and Short Rib are also top-notch.  For 2 people expect to spend around $80 to $100 with drinks and tip.  Portions are decent and satisfying.  The Full Chicken is really a FULL Sized Chicken.
You should absolutely try the ceviche! Tart, a bit of spice, very fresh.

(Translated by Google) The waitresses were extremely rude and provided the worst service however the manager came to apologize and invited us to come back so he could show us that they care about people. It is sad to see how a person's attitude can leave a good or bad taste in the mouth  (Original) Las meseras fueron extremadamente groseras y proporcionaron el peor servicio sin embargo el gerente vino a disculparse y nos invitó a regresar para poder mostrarnos que les importa la gente. Would recommend the bass.
Food was awesome!

OMG  I drove 2 hours to get some take out here, and I am ready to go again! Everything I ordered has a je ne sais quoi err is it no sé loc que about it.  Things that I would generally expect to taste a certain way, just taste better!  I stopped next door for tacos and beer for the ride home (beer when I got home) and all were lovely.  The to go packaging and instructions were well thought out, presented and done thoughtfully.  Love you!

This was probably one of the best meals I’ve had in Chicago. My husband and I got the striped bass, the Baja maki, the seasonal cocktail and seasonal dessert and WOW. The dessert was a fall inspired tres leches and it really did taste like fall exploded in my mouth. The service was also excellent. Highly recommend for a date night.
The staff and chefs are absolutely amazing! The food is like an experience of a lifetime! Absolutely perfect music and food and people. I'm so thankful for Lena Brava
This spot is fire. Came here on a late night for a burrito and I left so satisfied. Everything about the burrito was good. It's a great no frills spot to get your food on a late night.
Covid, Pick-up, Fail
Good was great

This is one of my fav places in the West loop. The Baja cuisine focused menu is exquisite, with several dishes that are vegetarian and seafood, great place for pescatarians.  They also have a great cocktail menu and wine list. I dine at Lena Brava regularly and highly recommend it

Had dinner at your fantastic restaurant last night.  The service was great and our waiter was more than helpful in recommending dishes.  Especially enjoyed the grilled octopus and bone marrow.  Also loved the ceviche as well as the sliced avocado appetizer.  Looking forward to coming back soon.
By far my favorite Mexican (and Rick Bayless) spot in the city of Chicago. This place will NOT disappoint!
This place is worth a try. They serve big portions for fair prices. Always well organized and with great vibes. Highly recommended.

Very well organised and accessible place. They serve large portions and for affordable prices. We loved the menu very much and the staff members were super personal and informative. I recommend this place.

My friend and I met for an early dinner. We decided to go with the tasting menu for 2. We had 2 starters, a small pasta course, the cod, tamal, and finished with a cherry tart with goat cheese cherry ice cream. All of it was delicious and we felt satisfied. Baja inspired, so flavorful and spicy. I had never had tamal before and I think that was my favorite dish. The vibe was low key. We were able to enjoy and savor the meal (and wines!) without feeling rushed. The whole staff were attentive.
Delicious, so favorable
Amazing. Food, service, wait time. Everything. Have been there multiple times and had great experiences.
Cool ambiance, helpful servers, delicious food and great drinks!
Great food but the tables are small and area is very close together

1. I know my photos are not the greatest 2. Lena Brava is highly underrated  I've lived in Chicago now for four years and have heard mixed reviews about Lena Brava. Well... not that much noise at all about the restaurant.  I went with two girlfriends for restaurant week and we were pleasantly surprised. Everything we ordered was so well done and the customer service was great.  I ordered the ceviche, scallops and wood oven tart. My friends also tried the pineapple aguachile, short rib, arroz con verduas. Every dish was delicately put together, the flavors were unique, and every bite was savored.  Not only was the food great, but the wait staff was all very kind and knowledgeable about the food and wine being served. We asked for wine recommendations and were kindly helped.  This would be a great spot for a first date or even a client/work dinner.
Lena Ceviche was absolutely delicious. Scallops are the correct 3rd course choice for restaurant week. Try the Herb is the Word cocktail.
Great food

Decided to check it out for restaurant week. Was not disappointed. Traditional Mexican with a twist I'd say. Will definitely go back to try it for dinner. Also make your life easier and make reservations through their website.
Terrible service. All the food was too spicey. Not a good experience at all.
Their fideo and ice cream/apple tart was to die for! Definitely go with the Leña Brava Experience! Worth every cent! Maybe have a flight at Cruz blanca after. #westloopbestloop
As a now visiting Chicagoan, Chicago is lucky to have places like this. Excellent food and drinks.
Still my favorite restaurant in Chicago
Solid menu with a good of variety of excellent dishes. The pescado a la talla is phenomenal, as is the rib eye. Good place for brunch.
Delish!   We had the fish, amazing!  Ceviche was very good.  Sharing items is advised so can try more.
Nice environment and the food was really yummy.
Relaxed with alot of charm. Our food was very good. The whole menu is well above average. Service is typically good. Prices were fair for the quality of the food. Give them a try.
Probably my favorite Bayless spot.
Delicious food, elevated atmosphere, and knowledgeable staff - all of the things you'd expect from a Bayliss spot.

Order early and don't come super-hungry!  Food was amazing and we got to try several different dishes as we were a group of 10 and shared. I think this is our favorite of the Bayless restaurants. But the ordering process and time to get our food was excessive (40+ min from ordering to receiving dessert; also, waiter still hadn't come by to get dinner order by the time our ceviche arrived). We were hungry when we got there; starving when dinner arrived (had to order an extra ceviche and side to ride us over); and ready to cancel dessert and leave except is was my birthday and the group wanted to have sweets.  They also really don't do apps and no bread or chips at the table, so put in ceviche and dinner order all at once and consider dessert before completely done w/ dinner. Unless you want to have a 3 hr dinner like us. So a 5 for the food, and a 3 for all the waiting (service itself was pretty good tho).  Bayless' brewery Cruz Blanca is right next door for pre- or post-dinner beers. But no flights or tasters like EVERY OTHER brewery, unfortunately.

Rick Bayless has done it again. His newest place features Baja specials paired with great drinks and wines. Too often, our idea of Mexico is a mishmash of regions; he will call it out for you, so you can see the different cuisines. It's a charming place, friendly and well-served. Order a lot and just taste all the great stuff offered. It's a must-see place in Chicago.
Food
Very exclusive place, culture, clean, very sophisticated dishes, food wonderfully served.  I recommend connoisseurs of exclusive cuisine.

Food was good but small portions, small wine pours, and poor service from wait staff and manager. Waitress was annoyed we didn’t bite on her up-sells. We waited an hour for apps, half hour/hour between courses. After notifying management, no effort was make to remedy the situation. Skip this place.

Food was good but portions are small. The biggest problem was the service. We did a 4 course menu that was more like a 4 course sampler. After 1:45 we were only on course 2. Neither the waiter nor the manager particularly cared and although something went clearly wrong, there was no offer to make it right.

Very good service, good drinks and good food selection. Good atmosphere, good location in Chicago. A little pricey for what you get, but looks like you pay for everything including the grill fire you see when you walk in. Bottom line, good place when you want to spend some good time and some extra dollars. We went there 3 or 4 times, probably we will go again. Sometimes reservation can be a challenge. We had good time each time we went there... I recommend at least one visit and the you decide for yourself if yount to visit again.
Food is good. Drinks are super expensive.
(Translated by Google) Excellent food.  (Original) Exelente comida.
It was so good we went two nights in a row!
One of my new favorite places. The cod al pastor and short rib was amazing
Great food! Very beautiful presentation!
Loved the place! The food was fantastic
Breathtaking menu, exactly what I expected and more. I wish I live close by to go to all restaurants of the chain more often.

Disappointing visit.  Lena used to be one of my favorites.  Our server seemed at first very attentive until we did not bite on her upsells so most of her attention went to other tables.  She also forgot a couple of our apps.  And then, when some other guy served our pork , we asked that it be sliced and his response was "well I gave you a knife" Unreal.  He then rethought his answer and took it back to the kitchen for slicing.  The pork was void of any flavor...very disappointing.  The chicken was good. Lena Brava is not what it once was.  Maybe just a bad night.
Great food and cocktails!
Bold takes on Mexicanizing cuisine that you wouldn't typically expect. Thoroughly enjoyable. But leave the non-explorers at home!
We wanted to go to one of Rick Bayless' places, and we chose Lena Brava. It did not disappoint. I loved my chilaquiles, and my ordered the Classic Mexican Breakfast.
Baja Mexican cuisine, done respectfully and masterfully. Great selection of mezcals and tequilas as well. Servers and bartenders know their business too, making smart suggestions all around.

Delicious food and fabulous service! Great vibe. The oysters were to die for, with amazing sauce and salsas to taste with them. Only thing is $29 scallop meal was 3 scallops...absolutely out of this world and cooked perfectly...but 3
Quite possibly the worst person I've ever had take care of us, Paul was arrogant, dismissive and never made us feel welcome. Its loud and the portions are small. No thanks!
I just love their food. I always get excellent customer service there. The place is clean and the staff members are always nice. Would recommend to others.

The execution of every dish is well thought out and amazing.  The way that they have the have kitchen set up let's the diner see how fresh the process is.  I tried cod al pastor and the octopus dish.  Each could be included in my favorite dishes of 2018.  Chef Baylee's did it again!

The dining room on the second floor has a really great atmosphere. Food is good but portions are very small, like most upscale restaurants. All the beers are from some local brewery or something so most people won't recognize anything on the beer menu. You'll just have to go by description and the waitress/waiters suggestions. Overall, glad I gave it a chance. Nice place to spend a evening.
Great food
Ceviche, sea bass, fire roasted tart, cocktails, wine 👍👍👍👍👍
Beautiful presentations of uniquely prepared food. Every bite was memorable, Especially the striped bass and pork shanks!
Very good food.  Fresh fish...what matters most.  And well prepared.

I am rating this a 1 star for a few reasons.  I totally understand people and companies make mistakes but it's in which how they correct them that's the difference maker.  The food was mediocre, nothing special but nothing bad.  However, we waited for over an hour for one of our desserts with no updates or apologies.  On top of that I received a $175 parking ticket in which their valet service had gotten me and was only made aware once I received it in the mail.  I emailed and called the restaurant over a 2 month period with no response.  Needless to say we will not be going back to here or any affiliated restaurants.  The ability to rectify the situation was non-existent.
Real good food

Service here is outstanding! Very kind and helpful. The interior is really neat. The food is delicious with only a few misses. The octopus is totally worth trying. The crab cakes were lacking acidity and salt. The braised chicken is a must have. I mean overall the menu offers a lot and you can’t go wrong trying this spot out.

Exceptional food with lots of choices and geared towards sharing. Prompt service with excellent recommendations from the menu. I will definitely go back, one of the best meals I have had in a long time!

Trying out Rick Bayless's Lena Brava. The starters came out terrible while the short rib saves the day (the mains were wayyy better)  The chips were burnt, wood fire is cool if you complement the flavors. It is not hip or fancy to char everything for the sake of it. The mocktail tasted like syrup.  Order the seafood and short rib. Avoid the uni, the uni wasn't sweet and the bread was too sturdy and heavy which overwhelms the uni and ceviche.
Interesting menu, the Striped Bass and Short Ribs were delicious!
Alway a great place to eat and socialize. Great food and great costumers service. Best Mexican food in town.

I went with friends for a birthday dinner, and with a lot of trepidation.  I've not been a fan of Bayless restaurants and my family had told me that the food here was not very good.  It was a warm night and upon entering the restaurant I was greeted by the hostess and the burning wood fire oven.  Needless to say, I was warmer now.  Thankfully we were seated on the second floor and the AC was very very nice here, almost too nice..... There were 9 of us seated so we all had the 5 course Baja Experience.  First course: leña ceviche and ceviche maki roll.  I thought both were very good, though I preferred the maki over the ceviche.  Much more flavors in the maki. Second course: Fideos.  This was an angel hair pasta in a green Chipotle sauce.  I liked this as it reminded me of a dish my aunt in Mexico used to make me when I was missing American food. Third course: braised short rib and tamal. The ribs were so delicious.  I was grabbing at it with my tortilla right off the bone.  The tamal was interesting as it was  polenta style and was topped with vegetables.  Not like Mom used to make.  It was ok. Fourth course: striped bass.  This was the star of the night.  Wow.  I loved this and ate half of the dish.  It was really great and I could have had my other friends portions on the other side of the table. Fifth: the wood oven tart.  I'm not one for desserts but this was very good.  See photo.  These were very good sized portions too.  I did not leave hungry.  But I did leave very very cold.  I sat under an AC vent and it did not turn off all night.  I probably could have asked to change it but I took one for the patrons.  But I was freezing.  I would return and try their carnitas, to see just how similar and different it is from traditional carnitas.  Oh, and drinks were very good.  Try a spicy margarita, with mezcal.  I loved it.  Thought margaritas are not on the menu, I ordered one, and the waitress chuckled when I did.  Maybe it's just something they really don't want to do but hey, I'm the customer! 😊
Perfection!
Excellent, complex, spicy, smoky, rich dishes. Great service. Nice ambiance.
Inspire recipes, perfect service, incredible wood fired rustic fruit tart for dessert.
Great and interesting food. Excellent service. Lovely outdoor dining and beautiful indoor dining as well. Rick Bayliss scores another perfect 10!
Food is extraordinary and service is great!
The food was AMAZING! My husband and I went here for our 1 year anniversary and every single item we tried was to die for! Would definitely be coming back here!
We hosted a dinner here with friends from Europe and Lena Brava killed it. Our friends have been talking about the meal ever since. I would give LB ten stars if I could.

I enjoyed the tasting menu here recently. It gives one an opportunity to sample a wide variety of dishes from a rather interesting menu. I chose 5 courses and found the portions to be ample. All of the dishes i tried were interesting and had different flavors...very savory! The stripped bass course offered an habañero  sauce as an option... and boy was it spicy... and i love spice....totally awesome. My only complaint was the occasional use of mayo on some dishes... it’s 2019.... mayo adds a stupid amount of calories an mutes the other flavors... not overly intricate. The black cod cooked perfectly and exceptional. Overall, great meal and I would happily return!
Service was the best as well as the presentation and quality of food. Blackened cod and Arctic Char were the best.
Awesome place.
Full of flavor

Perhaps Rick Bayless' worst concept. I did not enjoy any of the dishes. I found the food to be under seasoned or over seasoned (i.e. super spicy.. to the point of inedible).  Frontera Grill, Topolabombo, and Xoco are better representations of Bayless' food.

I dined for my birthday on 7/21. The restaurant is nice and cosy. The latin music is excellent!!  As for the menu  I ordered the braised beef. It came with cauliflower mash potatoes.  (Cauliflower Mash was delicious) The beef was good, however, I didn't care for the "fat" that was on the beef. For the price I paid for this entree, my meal came on a small plate. I was still hungry and bummed! My husband ordered spicy blue jumbo shrimp. He enjoyed the shrimp.  We ordered 2 sides: fingerling poatoes and swiss chard. The potaotes were tasty. I didn't like the swiss chard because the vinegar and some other seasoning that tasted gross.  My server was so sweet to bring a birthday treat for me (pistachio ice cream with crumbled cookie and hibiscus jam) the jam was a tad too tart for my liking. I did enjoy, the icecream and crumbled cookie.  Would I come back? Maybe  Be sure to order several dishes to taste from so you can get a taste of what the restaurant offers.
Fabulous!
It's a nice place, with a different approach to Latin food. The ceviche and salads were very good but I didn't like the soft shell crab, it felt I was chewing the entire 🦀

The enchilada plate and chicken quesadilla were really good. The breakfast tacos were above average. The Mexican rice and their Pinto beans were just average; no real taste. The free chips when you check in were good and the salsas were also good. The decor was good.
Favorite in the city.  Bayless is a master at cocktails and food.  Highly recommend!
(Translated by Google) Excellent place!!! It was worth visiting  (Original) Excelente lugar!!! Valió la pena visitarlo
Cooking over wood?! What more can you ask for. Great flavor, the chicken is amazing
Very interesting and flavorful food.  Good cocktails.
Ceviche heaven
Been here 3x and had a great experience for the most part. Very delicious alcoholic drinks. Food is amazing 2/3 experiences. Lovely staff, very attentive.
AMAZING experience, from the mezcal, food, and atmosphere, everything was top notch. Highly recommended for a celebration or date night.
Really great service and food. Siting on the bar watching the cooks making dishes was delightful. The Michoacán avocado Salad was delicious! And all vegetables are a great choice.
The chicken and cauliflower mash are my favorite! It's only open for dinner though, and they dont do orders to go!

Very lively, fun, casual spot from Bayless.  I really enjoyed the fresh, light take he is presenting with a heavily seafood oriented menu.  As usual for Bayless the flavors are bright and vibrant.  The menu has a "cold" section for more raw preparations and a hot side from the wood fired grill and oven.  We started with the Lena from the Ceviche menu. Great flavor from the green chile and not too spicy - just a little heat on the back of your tongue. It develops nicely.  We also had the Uni, Pan Campo (Uni Flatbread) which is definitely in the running for my favorite dish of the year. Uni, Albacore, and spicy avocado mash (habanero and wasabi, yum!) on a fresh crispy flatbread.  So much texture, so much flavor, so much going on.  This was a really great dish and a must for you Uni seekers.  It is worth making the trip just for this.  Grilled Endive, Chipotle, and Blood Orange salad was terrific.  Orange, Turnip, and Fennel combined for a flavorful team and again lot's of good textural interplay, along with the bright of the citrus and smokiness of the Chipotle.  Not sure how Bayless layers in so many flavors for each dish, but he is like the Frank Lloyd Wright of flavor.  Mains were both delicious.  On a chilly night in Chicago the Seafood Pozole really hit the spot.  Wonderfully flavorful broth did need a bit of spicing up (which we were eagerly provided by our server) so this is probably good news for those of you who are spice averse. Black Cod was delightful.  But the can't miss item was one of the side dishes - Corn Masa "Polenta."  Sweet, creamy and popping with corn flavor.  I could have eaten it by the bowl full.  You get this and the Uni Flatbread and you can die a happy person - keto be damned.
Great food & drinks. Great place for a night out or date night.

This was such a delightful culinary experience. Our waitress was amazing. The drinks were unique and very tasty. You can’t make a bad choice on the menu from apps all the way to dessert. Such a great twist on traditional Mexican cuisine. The plantains were my favorite because they reminded me of home.

Went here for brunch and it was $50 for a salad and 2 vodka sodas. They wanted to charge me $6 for soda water on TOP of $11 vodka. Absolutely ridiculous, the manager tried to tell me that every place charges this but most places I go to charge $7-10 for vodka soda with the SODA water Included. Honestly, I wish I would have never stepped foot in here, waste of $50.

Lena Brava serves modern Baja Mexican food.  The majority of the menu offerings are small plates with cooked and cerviche menu items. The mains are decent sized portion but if you are hungry probably not enough to get full. I really enjoyed the food here and the servers were quite attentive.  Food: 4.25 stars Service: 4 stars Environment: 3.75 stars Overall: 4 stars Recommendations: crab and uni, cod, beef short rib, rhubarb tart  The mains were really the stars here. The short rib was fall off the bone tender and there really is no need for a knife. The cod was equally delicious and I would recommend ordering both these dishes.  Of the small plates I had the crab, uni, avocado dish is the one I liked the best. Most dishes are usually paired with some type of starch (tortilla or chips). The only thing I didn’t really enjoy was the broccoli rabe because it was too bitter for my tastes.

I'm a concierge, and I've called countless restaurants.  But I've never dealt with a more rude, arrogant or unhelpful staff in my entire career.  I would get better service at a popeye's.  If politely asking to speak with a manager to help with a VIP is cause to make me to wait for 10-minutes, then hang up on me, and then not answer, then imagine how they would treat our guests!  I'll make sure to steer our guests away.  I would recommend you do the same.
Food was good, but our waitress could not have cared less about us. Wouldn't go back based on the flat, emotionless, service.
Brilliant dishes in Rick Bayless' s seafood focused restaurant. Beautiful dishes.  Upscale without the pretentious atmosphere. Friendly staff. Great drinks. Best chips from the open fire kitchen.
Just right. Delicious, quite tasty and perfect to share with the whole table.
Haven't eaten here, but the drinks and parties are so awesome!
Amazing food. Baja inspired. The striped bass tacos are a must get!

Great food, the staff was great and accomodating.  The only issue was the group of "bros" at the next table but that is not the restaurant's fault.  I blame absent parenting and a culture of #MEFIRST.

If you’re in Chicago around West Loop you have to try this place out. This restaurant is inspired by Mexican food and Baja California taste. I come from San Diego Ca which Ive visited Baja many times and love the taste of sea food down there. This place here in chicago has a great taste just like Baja. 5 starts on food for sure!

The sauce portions are too much and kill the balance of the plates. The cocktails are also pre-made. That kills the fine dining out of the place and makes you think chain restaurant managing expenses. This place is trying too hard to be authentic and unique. The ceviche is at best poke and should rename the aguachile

Amazing food. Share plates... you cannot make a bad choice.  The cauliflower was life changing... that kind of good. Casual atmosphere... but seriously good food.  Attention to detail and flavor is evident in each dish.  We will be back.

The cocktails to begin: tried fire and ice and both were tasty; very strong.  Food was great, as expected. We got a lot more than expected. I feel that what is meant to serve 2 could serve 3 or 4.  The service was good if not a little overbearing. (He was really trying to earn his tip.)  It was packed a little too close for comfort, but then again it was a Wednesday night and the clientele must have been from the suburbs because the polite Chicagoans I'm accustomed to did not surround me.
Unusual, excellent food ,noise
Everything we ordered was good. Cocktails were very good.
The staff and chefs are absolutely amazing! The food is like an experience of a lifetime! Absolutely perfect music and food and people. I'm so thankful for Lena Brava
Great food. Good service.

We enjoy the ambience, but I didn't appreciate the waitress adding $$ without verifying if we wanted it or not. We went with the multiple course dinner preset and she added the sea bass on without verifying with us, which added quite a bit to the bill.

Overall very tasty food, with interesting twists, extremely attentive hosts/servers/bartenders, good liquor options, and comfy environment.  I sat downstairs and although I had a great time, I wish I would have called/reserved earlier to get better seats.  Overall, great experience. Thank you

First thing you need to know, get your wallet ready because this place is expensive, (way to overpriced in my opinion).  I ordered the Tomahawk Steak ($90.00 Dollars dish) , the waitress told me it was enough for 2 people but that was a lie because that was a portion for one person, plus the steak wasn't even hot, I think that if you are paying $90.00 Dollars for a dish the less they can do is to served it Hot right?  So I noticed that they have scallops on the menu so thought why not, it was a $30.00 dollars dish so I was thinking (they must give you a good portion right) so I ordered 2 of those and what was my surprise when the scallops arrived? A plate with 3 scallops medium size with some yellow mole salsa, I'm sorry but to me that was just ridiculous and the scallops were OK, nothing special, so they are charging $10.00 per scallop, I don't know about you guys but to me that's a joke.  Anyway, if you are interested in trying this place just be ready to pay for overpriced regular food my friends.   👎🏼👎🏼👎🏼👎🏼

We stopped in here after having dinner at El Ché. We sat upstairs in the bar area, which overlooked the street. My husband enjoyed his beer and cocktail and I loved the mussels, and the chocolate dessert. We watched all the lyft and ubers drop people off and even got to see how quickly a boot is put on a vehicle, and even better the couples reaction when they saw what had happened. If your in the area this place has great views, an amazing dessert menu, cocktail list and selection of beers.
Delicious, thought out food
Outstanding Mexican. A tad bit pricey tho
Very interesting and flavorful food.  Good cocktails.  Only complaint is that the portions are small.  It would be nice if entrees came with a side or 2 on the plate. Ceviche appetizer is great.
Aight $$$$
Excellent customer service and food is amazing
Great for large groups Flavorful food and a very interesting menu. Highly recommend a visit.
First time visiting this place and couldn't be more satisfied, all the food tasted amazing and the staff is very friendly. Would highly recommend to everyone.

First time going and everything was great, looking forward to going again. Def start with the oysters and a mezcal flight, we did and weren't disappointed. Also highly recommend the Octopus, was some of the best we've ever had.
Oh my! The fish, the fish, the fish! Soooo delicious!

so while the service and vibe is in keeping with what everyone expects from Rick Bayless, the food was really disappointing. the shrimp and pork meatballs were bland, the black cod while well cooked was not well composed. the broccolini was contrived. we have been Frontera Grill and Topolobampo fans since the beginning so next time we want a taste of Rick’s cuisine we will opt for them.
All seafood dishes were so tasty! Highly recommended!
Nice bar

We started out with the Shrimp Al Mojo which is almost a dish in itself then we ordered the Salt Baked Arctic Char Fish (highly recommended) there is a 45 minute wait for this be it is well worth it. We added the Broccoli Rabe, Sweet Potato and 2 Tepache (drinks!) all of these were a great add on. We also tried the Verde Vacation and Baja Breeze both were very unique and will try again. We then finished the meal with the Wood Oven Tart dessert that was recommended to us and it was excellent. Plus the service was excellent Genaro gave us excellent recommendations throughout the night.
Amazing food. Highly recommend sharing entrees with the table, you will want to try everything. Wine list is phenomenal. Make sure to get a recommendation from the Sommelier.
The food was good with a wonderful experience and great service.

Absolutely delicious. Rick Bayless never disappoints. To drink we had El Diablo #2. It was almost like a dreamsicle with a hint of clove and orange after taste. The Hibiscus Beauty also didn’t disappoint. As the starter we chose the Leña Ceviche. It was so fresh and woodsie with the tortilla chips. We followed that with the Tamal, “Huevona” Salsa, Charred Brussels Sprouts. The tamal was cooked perfectly and would fall apart in your mouth. The wood fire after taste was very subtle and everything else was the perfect pairing with the tamal. Then we ordered the Pork Shank Carnitas, and if you want a Mexican experience, that’s the dish for you. The carnitas were perfect and also great for breakfast with leftovers. The salsa and beans made the perfect carnita tacos. As a side, we are the sweet potato, ancho, goat cheese. Delicious. Perfectly cooked and perfect blend of flavors under the wood fire. Last but not least, dessert....Chocolate Tamal Cake, melts in your mouth. The chocolate sauce is so rich and thick. The ice cream was a good balance and matched the candied amaranth alegria with the chocolate flavors. I can’t wait to go again!

Our first time at Leña Brava. It did not disaapoint. The service is imoecimpec. The drinks are amazing. Try the fire and ice mezcal cocktails. The housemade tortillas are to die for. Chris the manager came by and poured us glasses of champagne because it seemed we waited too long for a glass of water. Definitely coming back. Planning on checking out the next door as well.
Made a reservation to celebrate a brithday, let the hostess and waiter know and they completely forgot. Unfortunate because the food was great, hopefully they get the service together.
Visit this place everytime we go to Chicago
The Baja experience was a wonderful treat for a birthday dinner. Delicious food and drinks. A little retreat in snowy Chicago!
New favorite place. Must try the seabass! I was picking the bones clean.
Awesome high end mexican seafood. Rick Bayless
I’m always impressed by something when I visit . This last time I tried ceviche that had a hint of goat cheese and it was amazing! Also don’t skip the wine from Valle!
Nice try Rick.

We loved our experience at Lena breva this evening. The food is very inventive and unique, as many of Rick Bayless' places are. What made this restaurant stand out even more though was the staff. From the hostess to our waiter Donny to all of the chefs cooking food live in the background, everyone was friendly and inviting. We really enjoyed the presentation and taste of the tomahawk steak, a unique cut and wonderful main dish to share. We will certainly be back, and mostly due to the wonderful service.

Excellent service. Alexandra was very informative, friendly, and quite knowledgeable about all of the wine and mezcals. I would suggest seafood over other choices such as the pork carnitas and vegetable dish. Both of those left us underwhelmed. Couldn't get enough of the ceviche and al pastor black cod. The flavors were incredible.

A lovely experience! Highly recommend going. The tomahawk steak was to die for, great wine, and cocktails. The service was great with the exception of Adam the bartender, a pretty rude dude especially to my client. BUT don’t let this deter you. Just don’t sit at the bar.
Went in for a quick drink and snack. Was lucky enough to walk in and get a seat at the bar. Ordered the canela flip drink and oysters. Was impressed with both! Definitely recommend the place.

After a pretty lengthy search for a restaurant to check out during one of the few nights my wife and I get to enjoy a peaceful meal...we decided to go with LB, partly because it was Ricks place and also because we wanted to try Mexican.  We came in well before the dinner crowd and had reservation, sadly were seated by the connecting door to another restaurant and the cold draft was horrible.  Asked to be seated someplace else but apparently tables were taken.  No worries, we won’t fuss but do ensure the heat is up at least or perhaps not put a table there.  Waiter comes by, doesn’t explain the menu even though I read English...so I attempted to ask him what’s difference between various sections to the menu since there seemed to be appetizer type items in entree section.  Waiter disappears for good 13 mins till he came back finally to take our order, everything was ordered together since it seems like our waiter was a bit unreliable.  My wife ordered braised short rib, and I ordered the  Cod and we shared a ceviche.  The ceviche was extremely lemony and tart, we thought it may be how this is done at ricks place, so again did t make a fuss about it.  My cod was very good, however, presentation was horrible since it looked like the sauce settled like it was microwaved.  My wife’s short ribs were extremely dry, and after that we just decided to pay for our meal and got our dessert someplace else since it was just not a satisfying experience.
Fantastic time, great food, exceptional service. One of the best managed restaurants in the city.
Simply amazing.
Bad service and mediocre food.
Excellent experience.
Good cocktails. But the food was a bit too salty
First time here. They have really good food and great atmosphere. Everyone was super nice and helpful. I can't wait to visit again and take other family members.
The food and the atmosphere were the best. Wow
Phenomenal sea bass and ceviche. No, wait- everything on the menu was phenomenal.

Amazingly delicious ceviche and cold fish plates are the highlights here. The drinks were great too. The whole fish was also a wonderful shareable highlight. I'd veer away from the short rib and scallops, as they were decent but not as good as the other plates.

We had a great experience here. The food, the mezcals, the service, and the setting were all great. Elevated Mexican food with some surprising flavours. A little hard on the wallet but worth it for a special night out.

The best tacos I've ever feasted on. Period. My brother and I came around midday for a quick bite. The line in this place was always consistently nearly out the door. All the booths and tables were taken, but people quickly eat and leave, so it was a quick turnaround. I got two tacos (carnitas and carne asada) and a side of rice and beans. Although the rice and beans fell short, the tacos did not. The service was great also. Would definitely come back when I get a chance to come back to  IL- Cash only!!!

Entire staff is a true version of professionals, food was on point and spot on with the right amount of salt, fat, & acid. Highly recommend the Octopus, grilled tamale, black cod, mussels. They give you house tortillas throughout the meal to make tacos (because who doesn't want to make a taco out of anything delicious). Thank you for a great experience Lena Brava! CHEERS!

Rick Bayless never fails. I have been a fan of his for so many years, watching his shows on PBS. I have admired his passion for Mexican foods, he is so much into it to the point that sometimes I truly believe he is serenading all these exotic ingredients!😊 tonight's my husband and I we went to his restaurant Linea Brava in Chicago, we came from Michigan and I can tell you, the quality is excellent and it's worth every penny, for those who knows the art of food and the explosions of spices and herbs in your mouth. We will surely come back again. Our night was very memorable and the staff was simply wonderful.
Amazing, pricy food.

Love this restaurant. Great, interesting Mexican food. None of that horrible cheese covered fare that is so often sold as Mexican food. Decent mezcal at a reasonable price. Got a whole grilled fish and I felt like I was back on the beaches of Oaxaca. Service wasn’t as great as the rest of it, but we were on the second floor in a corner (not my favorite table location).
Upstairs bar is great and their beers offer a wide selection sure to meet your pallet's needs. Every time get good attention and details from the bartenders.

The food was really good, but the service was extremely terrible!   Took forever for the food to arrive to the table, 3 1/2 hours is ridiculous for a good table of 8!  Really disappointed, with all they hype.
Great....just great

Food has been amazing every time but the service has suffered to an untenable level. 45 minutes after a reservation to get seated, another 15 for the waiter to show up, and nary an apology (and this has happened more than once -- shame on me for being fooled twice). The food may be good but it's not worth the aggravation anymore.

Meh.  Bizarre pacing of dishes/drinks, excessively loud music, and service errors led to an overall experience not commensurate to the quality of the food.  The food itself is quite good but the experience was a bit frustrating.

This is now my new favorite restaurant to bring out of town guests to show off the Chicago culinary scene. It shouldn't be a surprise that everything came out perfect and the service was attentive. The menu is adventurous but very solid, focusing a bit more on seafood. The cocktails were complex and sophisticated (i.e. layers of flavors). I'm not an oyster person (too many disappointments in the past) but the oysters here were excellent. I'd highly recommend this as a starter. I finished the striped bass that's meant for two by myself - it's that good. We had the tart for dessert - to me it was good but I'd skip that next time and have another cocktail.
This place is amazing. Every single plate we tried was outstanding, and the drinks as well. The chef knows how to bring out the flavors and does it perfectly. We will definitely be back.

We had a fantastic meal here on a Sunday evening. The fish was very fresh and a very large, shareable dish. Everything else we had was authentic and unique as well. The one caveat is this place is definitely pricey. I wasn't really expecting it, but I should have done some more research prior to going!
The salt-baked Artic Char was wonderful!
Was ok

Fantastic food, fantastic staff... What more can you ask for? That pineapple/goat cheese appetizer as a big hit and the wood oven tart to end the meal was one of the things best things I have eaten in a long time... Everything else was solid, but those two dished stood out for me!
Fantastic food, but wasn't quite worth the hour long wait for food.  On a busy night, just come prepared to wait.

Great service and delicious food.  The food was beautiful and flavorful.  If you want just enough spice ; not too hot, but just enough to play on your lips, this is the place.  The highly recommend the pineapple goat cheese and salsa macha aguachile, the yellowtail belly ceviche and the Baja coctel.  Finish it off with the flourless chocolate cake with the strawberry-jicama salsa.  It was amazing...not too sweet, lots of chocolate flavor, and interesting textures.
Superb,  interesting food
I think you get a better deal ordering off the menu than you do through the tasting menu.  Portions are bigger and you save money overall.
Really good food and drinks. Good service and staff. Can get noisy but it's cozy and fun.

Food and ambiance was on point. Had the butterfly bass, chicken, and quail as mains. However, took off a star for 45 min wait pass reservation time and another star for many hard bones in the butterfly fish. I'm used to eating fish with bones but a bit surprised to find it on a filet without any warning. Swallowing an unintended fish bone is a horrible experience which I had experienced as a kid and the trip to the hospital is not fun so just watch out for those hard bones along the spine and tail and hope the restaurant can do a better job with the warning or remove the bones better

My husband and I shared the bass fish for two, Nayarit-style. It's the best whole fish in all of Chicago! So delicious! Just watch the bones in the middle and the periphery. And definitely take advantage of asking for more hand-made, addictive corn tortillas. They're amazing! 😍
Great Rick Bayless restaurant. The black cod was fantastic and great specialty drinks

Wonderful experience. Sat upstairs and it was relatively quiet (which I preferred) compared to the lively atmosphere downstairs. Patrick was our server and he did a fabulous job. It was a slower night (Tuesday) so we were able to linger with no issues. The cocktails are unique and well prepared. From the smoky Aero-Mexico to the citrusy dry Tamarindo. The Uni Pan de Campo Serrano was an amazing start. So many flavors to choose from. The octopus with squid ink sauce was cooked to perfection with a smoky flavor. Pescado En Su Sugo was delicious on a black bean purée. He sides are tasty and portions size is decent. The fixed price menu is a good value but it does not offer much variety. Overall Leña Brava is on the pricey side but well worth it.

We always enjoy Rick Bayless restaurants and finally made it out to Lena Brava. Very enjoyable if not quite everything we had hoped for. We went with the Baja experience tasting mega which I would not recommend only because it actually turned out to be more than ordering the same dishes separately. Highlights were fall off the bone ribeye in luscious Padilla sauce served over what I thought were some kind of grits but were actually cauliflower. Barber on that one. Scallops also excellent mainly due to the mole. Not quite as good were appetizers. An average cervice. Hi Ramada good but served on ice cold stone that froze the accompanying sauces. Corn crackers served with apps was burnt.  But then a wonderful fruit tart with raspberry sorbet. Outstanding mezcal menu that server didn’t know much about. Pours very much on the might side. Service in general was acceptable but not too attentive.  Some great things about this meal. Some not so much. Overall an enjoyable night. Not sure if I’d go back, but I’d recommend trying it at least once.
Food was delicious. Service was stellar. Should be a moderately adventurous eater. But, again, food was absolutely fantastic.
Good food.
Love it! Waiter was on his A+ game. The Chicken, Caritas and the fish where delicious 😋
Great food, perfect service, and large portions.

Wow. They marked a menu just for me to help me navigate my dairy, egg and msg allergies! And oh my the sea bass was incredible as well as the shishito peppers, Leña and uni (our first experience with sea urchin). Excellent service and incredible food.
This was our second trip to Lena Brava and we brought our 7-year-old son. Terrific food and I love the bright and breezy atmosphere.

An outstanding dining experience that's better, if possible, than Frontera Grill. From the marvelous fire and ice cocktail, through the delicious tasting menu (including to-die-for ribs), supplemented by the outstanding ceviche maki roll app, plus an excellent bottle of Mexican viognier + fiano blend, how could you not love it? The wait staff was superb, especially the lead bar tender.  We sat at the bar and watched three talented women prep salads, ceviche and maki rolls at an amazing speed. Thank you Fernando at Frontera for recommending Lena Brava!
Food was good.  Price was very high. I will not come again.

(Translated by Google) Different Mexican dishes. They say they all use wooden grills without using a gas fire. It was delicious, but the amount was too small. Temple cuisine is recommended.  (Original) 색다른 멕시칸 요리들. 가스불을 사용하지않고 모두 우든그릴을 사용한다고해요. 맛있었지만 양이 너무 적었어요. 관자요리 추천합니다.

Everything was delicious. We had the avocado side to start. It came with a small bowl of crispy grasshoppers you could use to garnish. Crunch crunch! We ordered the short rib, black cod and the tamal with a side of summer squash. It was all good but the cod and tamal were the standouts.  I had the Barleybomba barleywine beer from next door - it was superb. My dinner mates were likwise pleased with their cocktails.
Amazing.
Delicious dishes and drinks!
Didn't have any food but the cocktails and ambiance were great!!

Service was great but we were pretty disappointed in what we got for the price we paid.  *Ceviche was delicious!*  The one dish we got with The Baja Experience (I believe it was Hiramasa Laminado) was terrible, the whole plate was a big stone with inedible garnishes, we didn't know what part we could actually eat.
Amazing food and cocktails. Ceviche and Hamachi rocked. Probably has the best selection of Baja wines in the country and the mezcal cocktails are fantastic.

Was excited to come here. Looking for authentic wood fired and raw deliciousness. Food was ok. Seemed to be trying too hard, but missed on some of the basics. We had a sashimi like appetizer. It was decent. The fish was super fresh, but lacked flavor. Entrees were the scalllops and carnitas. Both were decent, but not great. Mole sauce with the scallops lacked the richness that a mole usually has. Carnitas was good, but a bit dry. Cocktails were good. All were good, but premium price expect consistent excellence.
Amazing unique dishes and very attentive service.
We had a terrific time! Food was delicious and perfect for sharing the striped bass platter, black cod and pineapple appetizer we're delicious.
Great unique food.  Service was good to start but after we received our entrees it was as if we were forgotten about.  Once I went to the host stand to comment the server got back on point.
Can't be beat.

The cocktails are as incredible as the food, and the food is no joke. My friend and I did the tasting menu. It was perfectly sized to let you have a good portion of everything without feeling overly full or like you barely got to try it. Whatever you go with, the side of plantains is a good choice.
Amazing take on Mexican food.
Excellent service!!! Excellent food!!!
A must go restaurant. Unbelievable flavors, slow cooked meats, flawless execution.

Food was excellent. I had the Tamal, which was vegetarian, and very good. I also tried the plantains on the side, and that was great, too. One friend got the short rib and another friend got the Halibut. Both agreed that everything was delicious. I personally feel that upstairs is the best place to be seated. The menu is divided up into "Ice" dishes, which are cold, and "Fire" dishes which are hot. The only minor complaint I have is that my Tamal didn't have as much spice as I had expected. But, I didn't ask for more spice either. Overall, it's a great restaurant that I'll definitely come back to!
Everything was delicious! I'll be coming back many times!

To be honest this one star review is the result of high expectations, mediocre food, and poor service. We made reservations for 9:00 PM but did not receive our entrees until well after 10:00. We had two appetizers that for some reason were spaced 20 minutes a part. The oysters were full of shell debris and grime. The steak was 7/10 but the fist underwhelming. Honestly, if I could do the whole night again, I'd much rather keep it simple at small cheval with a friendly, inviting environment, and food appropriately priced. Maybe this restaurant was a great find at one time; however, I now worry it is past its prime and riding the coat-tails of its former glory.
Excellent
Wonderful food and service, but painfully loud music.
Very good food.

Food was great. I was able to do the "Baja Experience" which allows you to taste a few of the dishes. Standaouts are the short rib, avocado salad, and ceviche. The drinks at creative and pretty delicious as well. It is a little pricey. Not many vegetarian options and the one we tried (the Tamal) wasn't very good.
The service was awesome and the food was perfect. Do not pass up the pork carnitas. They were Heaven. Beautiful whole wood fired fish. We were delighted and will be back when we are in town again
Delicious food, excellent service. Not inexpensive.
This was our first time here, we came for my wife's birthday, we were not disappointed, everything was delicious.

Love the fish a la leña, avoid the small dishes way to expensive for the size of the portions , Rick when I call your restaurant I don't need to hear your voice, take the ego for a walk , great service from the wait staff , the hostess needs to improve , it feel like they are doing me a favor by seating me at the restaurant,  But for sure I will go back for that Fish
Did not care for the food. I'm not sure why the high ratings but they're definitely not from any Mexicans who know flavor. Took 45 minutes to get seated on a Wednesday. I did like the kitchen set up.
The kod was to die for! Very interesting scallop Maki roll too.

The food was delicious and the service was great. Especially loved the pineapple aquachile and the short ribs. For dessert, we shared Amazon Chocolate Cake, a wood fired tart and cheesecake. Wonderful!
Good quality seafood.

Creative cocktails.   Solid wine list.  Outstanding selection of tequila & mezcal. Seafood intensive menu prepared thoughtfully with incredible ingredients.   Homemade tortillas are the icing on the delectable cake!

Best dinner I've ever had in Chicago. I thought it was reasonably priced for the offering and the experience.  I will definitely be coming back to Lena Brava.  It was a wonderful place to spend a cold winter evening with good friends.
Love this restaurant .... the food is amazing and the service is outstanding. The decor is cozy and comfortable.
They wouldn't serve grasshoppers if they weren't delicious. This place has delicious food, great service.

Cannot believe everything is cooked over a wood fire. Soo delish. Will go back for the Black Cod Al Pastor & Braised Shortrib. Both full of flavors & tender.
Amazing staff, magical food, great cocktails. A fantastic experience. Get the whole, grilled bass!
Went for restaurant week and all the food was delicious, although sometimes oddly presented. The service was courteous. We would go back again.

I ate there and was lucky to sit right next to the owner Rick Bayless who was entertaining some friends. Maybe thanks to his presence or maybe it's always this way.. but the service was the BEST I've ever had anywhere in my entire life. Food was truly delicious. Emmanuel, our server, made our experience much more enjoyable. He was very informative and well knowledged on the various dishes, which allowed us to make an educated decision based on our palet preferences.

Very good food and service.  The most impressive element is that this is a complete different restaurant than Rick Bayless's other places.  Different flavors and atmosphere.  A worthy visit to expand your definition of Mexican food!
Adam is the best! Quick drinks, amazing mixtures and flavor. Definitely a must stop and please visit the bartender Adam!

My friend and I came here on Tuesday at 5:30 without a reservation and were able to sit right away at the bar! I highly recommend showing up right when they open if you cannot get a reservation on open table. The food was superb and so was …
Excellent food. Very fresh and flavourful. A must go for Rick Bayless fans.
Excellent ceviche!!
Wonderful!
Rick never disappoints!   We really enjoyed his Restaurant Week 2018 menu.   For $44 it was really generous
Interesting regional Mexican cuisine (Baja). We also tried a Mexican wine from the same region—surprisingly good.

Rick Bayless is definitely on a roll, from winning a James Beard award to creating fantastic food with great ambiance at this restaurant. The food is definitely well worth the trip. This is an exceptional restaurant in the West Loop in Chicago. The service is outstanding, and the food quality is amazing. Every dish is flavorful and I highly recommend the full fish preparation. Excellent offering by a prize Chicago chef.
